es make all the difference\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eRazer\u0026#39;s managed to improve one of Android\u0026#39;s best controllers\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBut our main complaint about this device was that it was expensive, coming in with a retail price of $100. Luckily, we\u0026#39;re now seeing a solid deal that knocks half off, dropping it down to just $50 for a limited time. So if you\u0026#39;ve been thinking about buying a controller, now\u0026#39;s going to be a great time.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-razer-kishi-v2-controller\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Razer Kishi V2 controller?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Razer Kishi V2 controller really does deliver an experience that changes your gaming experience. You get a set of analog joysticks, buttons, triggers, and shoulder buttons. Basically what you\u0026#39;d find on other similar devices. But what puts the Kishi V2 over its competitors is that is has micro-switches that sit under the buttons and D-pad that feel quite good and are extremely responsive.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eIn addition, you also get nice attention to details like passthrough charging, along with special adapters that can make any phone feel secure and connected. While the plastic build might not appeal to everyone, it does provide an excellent balance, making the device durable and lightweight. For the most part, this is a superb device, and if you\u0026#39;re a frequent gamer, you should pick this up.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eFor the time being, you can score a hefty discount on the Kishi V2 as it drops to just $50. Or if you\u0026#39;re still on the fence, we can also \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/backbone-one-70-march-2025-deal/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003erecommend the Backbone One that\u0026#39;s now just $70\u003c/a\u003e. Of course, you can also check out our other \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/best-bluetooth-game-controllers/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003econtroller recommendations\u003c/a\u003e as well.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
